FBIS4-6560 "dreas078_n_94014" FBIS-EAS-94-078 Daily Report 19 Apr 1994 Vietnam Prices of Gold, U.S. Dollar Increase Prices of Gold, U.S. Dollar Increase BK2104094994 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 1100 GMT 19 Apr 94 BK2104094994 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network Vietnamese BFN [Text] It is noteworthy in today's market prices that the gold price increased by 1,000 dong per ounce in the south while in the north the price decreased. The U.S. dollar increased by 10 to 20 dong per dollar in the north and the value of Chinese currencies is also higher than the previous day in Lang Son Province and Hanoi. Rice in Ca Mau is 1,100 dong per kg, while in My Tho it is 50 dong cheaper. The price of agricultural products in central Vietnam is normal while the price of construction materials has increased in the north and decreased in the south.
